07:31.051 --> 07:33.042
Marion?

07:35.588 --> 07:36.953
- MARION: What is it, Howard?
- Richie, Joanie,

07:37.057 --> 07:38.252
get down here quick.

07:38.358 --> 07:39.883
MARION: What is it, Howard?
I'm busy. What...

07:39.993 --> 07:42.052
- I bought something.
- JOANIE: Ooh!

07:42.162 --> 07:44.597
- MARION: What? -A color TV
with a remote control!

07:44.698 --> 07:46.097
No, it's not a color TV.

07:46.199 --> 07:47.166
It's outside.

07:47.267 --> 07:48.291
- Outside!
- Outside!

07:48.401 --> 07:50.369
- You traded in the DeSoto!
- A car?

07:50.470 --> 07:52.529
- Look. -JOANIE: A new car?
- RICHIE: Where is it?

07:52.639 --> 07:54.437
Wh-Wh-Where...?
It's stolen.

07:54.541 --> 07:55.975
Oh...

07:56.076 --> 07:58.067
No, Marion. Right here.

07:58.178 --> 08:00.237
It's a new item for the store.

08:00.347 --> 08:02.076
Look at this.

08:04.851 --> 08:06.216
Oh, that's terrific.

08:06.319 --> 08:07.753
Got to get back upstairs.

08:07.854 --> 08:10.346
Jenny's in the middle
of a juicy piece of gossip.

08:10.457 --> 08:13.552
Something about the
football coach wearing a dress.

08:15.161 --> 08:16.560
Coach Bilford?

08:16.663 --> 08:18.427
I got a date.

08:18.531 --> 08:20.590
Well, Howard,
I have to fix dinner.

08:20.700 --> 08:22.065
Well, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

08:22.168 --> 08:23.829
A personalized doormat.

08:23.937 --> 08:25.996
I think it's gonna be
a big-selling item.

08:26.106 --> 08:28.006
Oh, but, Howard,
how many Cunninghams

08:28.108 --> 08:30.406
are there in Milwaukee?

08:31.978 --> 08:34.777
Marion, you can put
anything you want on it.

08:34.881 --> 08:36.178
Oh.

08:36.282 --> 08:37.613
How about "welcome"?

08:37.717 --> 08:38.912
(doorbell rings)

08:39.019 --> 08:40.350
Just answer the door, will you?

08:40.453 --> 08:41.614
Yeah, I got it.

08:42.889 --> 08:45.824
- Hi, hi, hi, hi, hi.
- Hey, Al.

08:48.561 --> 08:51.861
Something very important
came up, and I need your advice.

08:51.965 --> 08:53.763
Well, Al, as I told you
at Arnold's, I feel

08:53.867 --> 08:55.130
-that what you really need...
- Rich, Rich,

08:55.235 --> 08:56.566
- I was talking to your father.
- Oh.

08:56.669 --> 08:58.194
Of course, Al.
Come on in.

08:58.304 --> 08:59.567
What is it?

08:59.672 --> 09:02.471
Well, Howard, a man came
to see me from the, uh,

09:02.575 --> 09:04.566
Lake Michigan
Investment Company,

09:04.677 --> 09:06.111
and he wants to invest
in Arnold's,

09:06.212 --> 09:08.146
and he wants to expand it.

09:08.248 --> 09:09.773
Oh, isn't that
wonderful, Alfred?

09:09.883 --> 09:11.783
It sounds very exciting,
Al, but...

09:11.885 --> 09:13.979
well, maybe you shouldn't
rush into this.

09:14.087 --> 09:16.784
What do you know about
Lake Michigan Investments, huh?

09:16.890 --> 09:19.723
Well, nothing, but the guy's
a very nice person.

09:19.826 --> 09:21.191
Oh, sure, real nice.

09:21.294 --> 09:23.592
Wants to call our band
the Al Tones.

09:23.696 --> 09:25.926
Well, he may be nice,
but I still think

09:26.032 --> 09:27.431
you ought to check it out.

09:27.534 --> 09:28.968
To begin with, you ought to have

09:29.069 --> 09:31.094
your accountant
go over their books, and...

09:31.204 --> 09:33.468
and you'll need a lawyer
for the contracts.

09:33.573 --> 09:35.632
You hear that, Al?
Same advice I gave you.

09:35.742 --> 09:37.733
I have a nephew
who's almost a lawyer.

09:37.844 --> 09:40.836
He sent in this matchbook cover,
and six years later...

09:40.947 --> 09:42.346
Marion!

09:42.449 --> 09:43.939
He needs a lawyer now.

09:44.050 --> 09:45.449
Well, that's true.
Good luck, Al.

09:45.552 --> 09:46.986
Thank you, Marion.

09:47.087 --> 09:50.421
You know, Al, a franchise--
that's a lot of responsibility.

09:50.523 --> 09:52.184
You sure you want
to get into this?

09:52.292 --> 09:55.057
Well, Howard,
every man has his dream.

09:55.161 --> 09:57.630
And you know what my dream is?

09:57.730 --> 09:58.993
When I close my eyes,

09:59.099 --> 10:00.897
I see myself
walking along this road

10:01.000 --> 10:04.834
and I'm planting Arnold Burgers
as I go along.

10:04.938 --> 10:08.101
Just like... Johnny Appleseed.

10:08.208 --> 10:11.610
And sprouting up behind me
are thousands of drive-ins

10:11.711 --> 10:14.510
with people of every race,
color and creed

10:14.614 --> 10:17.242
coming up to me and saying,

10:17.350 --> 10:19.682
"Hold the onions, Al."

10:19.786 --> 10:22.721
Oh, that's a lovely dream.

10:23.890 --> 10:25.016
Well, I got to go.

10:25.125 --> 10:26.786
Wait a minute, Al.

10:26.893 --> 10:28.952
How would you like
one of these, uh,

10:29.062 --> 10:31.030
personalized doormats, huh?

10:31.131 --> 10:33.930
Oh, thanks, Howard.

10:38.872 --> 10:40.135
(chuckling)

10:40.240 --> 10:43.540
Two ice-cold glasses of milk.

10:43.643 --> 10:46.340
That's the way to start off
a business meeting.

10:46.446 --> 10:48.710
You got to keep a clear head.

10:48.815 --> 10:50.214
A.D.

10:50.316 --> 10:52.978
Oh, Mr. Holloway, come on in.

10:53.086 --> 10:54.110
Come in.

10:54.220 --> 10:56.086
Hey, have a nice glass of milk.

10:56.189 --> 10:57.088
No, no, thanks.

10:57.190 --> 10:58.089
