12:12.999 --> 12:15.331
Well, I guess this is it,
old girl.

12:16.369 --> 12:19.395
The end of the road.

12:19.505 --> 12:22.167
It was fate that brought us
to this moment.

12:22.275 --> 12:24.369
Fate.

12:24.477 --> 12:26.844
And a guy with an iron hand.

12:28.014 --> 12:31.507
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

12:33.653 --> 12:35.451
Al. What is this?

12:35.555 --> 12:36.920
What the heck is this?

12:37.023 --> 12:38.718
What are these?
What the heck are these?

12:38.825 --> 12:40.953
Rich, I'm taking a little trip.

12:41.060 --> 12:42.755
A little trip, huh?

12:42.862 --> 12:44.660
"Closed, for sale by owner."

12:44.764 --> 12:45.822
That's no little trip.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.559
Okay, I'm taking a big trip.

12:47.667 --> 12:49.726
What is going on, Al?
Come on.

12:49.836 --> 12:51.998
- Rich, okay, it's good news!
- Yeah?

12:52.105 --> 12:53.800
I sold out to Mr. Holloway.

12:53.906 --> 12:55.067
Lots of bucks.

12:55.174 --> 12:57.233
Boy, I'm gonna make it
on easy street.

12:57.343 --> 12:58.572
Oh.

12:58.678 --> 13:01.306
Oh, Rich, I can't lie to you.
He's a crook.

13:01.414 --> 13:03.815
He's got a gang, and one
of them's got an iron hand.

13:03.916 --> 13:05.907
Oh, they-they want
to take over Arnold's,

13:06.019 --> 13:07.180
and-and they want
to make Arnold's

13:07.287 --> 13:08.550
-into a bookie joint.
- What?

13:08.655 --> 13:09.918
Well, I-l got to go, Rich.

13:10.023 --> 13:11.752
I'll write you a letter
explaining everything later.

13:11.858 --> 13:13.917
Hey, wait. Why don't you
explain it to me now?

13:14.027 --> 13:16.155
Try and tell me how running away
is gonna help anything.

13:16.262 --> 13:17.730
Rich, don't you see?

13:17.830 --> 13:19.958
Selling the building's the
only way I'm going to stop them.

13:20.066 --> 13:21.295
They're crooks.

13:21.401 --> 13:22.596
Hey, Al.

13:22.702 --> 13:24.170
All right, look.
Don't you sign nothing.

13:24.270 --> 13:25.328
They're crooks.

13:25.438 --> 13:27.668
- Fonz.
- Yeah.

13:27.774 --> 13:29.833
You knew without me telling you?

13:29.942 --> 13:32.741
That happens.
It happens sometimes.

13:32.845 --> 13:34.142
Let me tell you something.

13:34.247 --> 13:36.215
Nobody's gonna push one
of my friends out of town.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.751
You understand that?
You just stay right here.

13:38.851 --> 13:40.114
I'll be back.

13:40.219 --> 13:41.709
- Fonz, Fonz.
- Yeah.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.188
Mr. Holloway's gonna
come back in one hour.

13:44.290 --> 13:45.815
Hey, that's enough time.
Don't worry about it.

13:45.925 --> 13:47.188
Richie, let's get
the gang together.

13:47.293 --> 13:48.783
- Right now.
- Right.

13:48.895 --> 13:51.387
Get the gang together, Fonz.

13:51.497 --> 13:54.797
Fonz, we don't have a gang.

13:54.901 --> 13:56.767
We don't have a gang.

14:00.907 --> 14:02.705
<i>RICHIE: Fonzie and!
called this meeting</i>

14:02.809 --> 14:04.106
for one very big reason.

14:04.210 --> 14:06.338
These thugs are trying
to push around Al.

14:06.446 --> 14:07.777
We can't let that happen.

14:07.880 --> 14:09.370
Got any more soda, Rich?

14:09.482 --> 14:10.881
No, we don't have any more soda.

14:10.983 --> 14:12.542
Do you have any ideas?

14:12.652 --> 14:14.017
- I got it...
- Ah, good.

14:14.120 --> 14:15.485
- I got it.
- He's got it.

14:15.588 --> 14:18.319
We send them
a threatening Candygram.

14:19.726 --> 14:22.195
I'm going to pretend
I didn't hear that, Malph.

14:22.295 --> 14:23.194
Hear what, Fonz?

14:23.296 --> 14:25.458
I got it-- we'll burn 'em out.

14:25.565 --> 14:27.556
I definitely didn't hear that.

14:27.667 --> 14:29.635
(louder):
We'll burn them out.

14:31.371 --> 14:32.736
I think we're
overlooking something.

14:32.839 --> 14:35.206
I mean, why don't we just
call the police, huh?

14:35.308 --> 14:36.332
- That's a great idea, Rich.
- Yeah.

14:36.442 --> 14:37.705
What are you going to tell 'em?

14:37.810 --> 14:39.073
Three guys want to buy
into Al's?

14:39.178 --> 14:40.646
Well... well, yeah,
you're right.

14:40.747 --> 14:41.908
They haven't done anything.

14:42.014 --> 14:42.981
Okay, okay, no police.

14:43.082 --> 14:44.516
But we have got to do something.

14:44.617 --> 14:45.675
Hey, I'm doing it.

14:45.785 --> 14:47.753
I'm keeping my ear
to the street, huh?

14:47.854 --> 14:50.448
Bet you get kicked
in the head a lot.

14:53.860 --> 14:55.225
All right, now, here's the info.

14:55.328 --> 14:56.921
This gang was kicked out
of Chicago

14:57.029 --> 14:58.497
for messing with the real Mob.

14:58.598 --> 15:00.123
All right, then he tried to move

15:00.233 --> 15:01.792
into Cleveland,
you know, lay low.

15:01.901 --> 15:04.734
He was kicked out by the PTA.

15:05.772 --> 15:07.171
Well, yeah, that was then.

15:07.273 --> 15:09.105
Now he's got this new thug.

15:09.208 --> 15:10.835
Guy they call the Claw.

15:10.943 --> 15:11.910
Claw?

15:12.011 --> 15:13.172
Yeah, man has an iron hand.

15:13.279 --> 15:14.405
(Ralph whimpers)

15:15.715 --> 15:16.944
All right, now, look.

15:17.049 --> 15:18.813
I know exactly
what these thugs are.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.408
Bullies-- that's it.

15:20.520 --> 15:22.648
Fonz, you're going to pound
these guys, right?

15:22.755 --> 15:25.383
I never use violence
unless I have to.

15:25.491 --> 15:26.890
All right, Rich,
now, you tell me--

15:26.993 --> 15:28.825
what are we supposed to do
against these guys?

15:28.928 --> 15:30.987
Hey, I'm telling you,
I know exactly what to do.

15:31.097 --> 15:33.259
You stand up to a bully,
he backs down.

15:33.366 --> 15:35.460
You know, that's what
my dad always says.

15:35.568 --> 15:38.037
Only way to deal with a bully--
stand right up to him.

15:38.137 --> 15:39.605
My dad told me to run.

15:40.907 --> 15:43.842
My dad told me to stand there
and take it like a man.

15:45.211 --> 15:46.940
Well, I think Fonzie's
got the right idea here.

15:47.046 --> 15:49.174
I mean, if we can just make
a show of force,

15:49.282 --> 15:50.272
those guys will back down.

15:50.383 --> 15:52.351
Oh, yeah?
That's what Custer said.

15:52.452 --> 15:53.544
Hey, I promise you, Ralphie,

15:53.653 --> 15:55.382
nothing is going to
happen to you.

15:55.488 --> 15:58.458
Oh, this is great.
We'll back those creeps down.

15:58.558 --> 15:59.889
No way.

15:59.992 --> 16:01.892
You're too young
for this kind of stuff.

16:01.994 --> 16:04.395
Oh, I'm too young
for all the neat things.

16:04.497 --> 16:07.432
Oh, you know, actually I'm
a lot younger than I let on.

16:09.068 --> 16:13.301
Ralphie, I promised you nothing
is going to happen to you.

16:13.406 --> 16:14.532
Fine. It's all settled.

16:14.640 --> 16:16.005
We'll meet at Arnold's at 10:00.

16:16.108 --> 16:17.166
- Great. Oh.
- Oh!

16:17.276 --> 16:19.472
And you do not tell our parents.

16:19.579 --> 16:21.411
Oh, what do you think I am,
a squealer?

16:21.514 --> 16:22.481
No comment.

16:22.582 --> 16:23.572
All right, any questions?

16:23.683 --> 16:25.117
Should we eat first?

16:27.186 --> 16:28.881
Sit down. Come on, let's have...
let's have this out.

16:28.988 --> 16:30.683
- All right. -Okay, uh,
first thing we need to do

16:30.790 --> 16:32.189
-is talk to Al, right?
- That's right. -Right.

16:32.291 --> 16:34.350
And then, look, we tell Al
to move right in, okay?

16:34.460 --> 16:36.258
Here's what we're going to do.

16:39.632 --> 16:42.329
Ah, this is crazy.

16:42.435 --> 16:45.405
Fonzie's plan
is never gonna work.

16:45.505 --> 16:47.974
I'm getting out of here.

16:53.412 --> 16:55.471
You look like you're in a hurry.

16:55.581 --> 16:58.175
You're not trying to run out
on us, are you, partner?

16:58.284 --> 17:00.082
No, I was just gonna
go outside and check

17:00.186 --> 17:02.120
to make sure you got
a good parking space.

17:02.221 --> 17:03.313
Ain't that nice?

17:03.422 --> 17:05.083
- You're a good boy.
- Yeah.

17:05.191 --> 17:06.386
Hi, Leo.

17:06.492 --> 17:08.256
You're a real sweet boy.

17:08.361 --> 17:09.829
Hi, Mr. Holloway.

17:13.465 --> 17:15.491
Hi, Mr. Claw.

17:15.601 --> 17:18.536
Well, here are the papers,
right from the lawyer.

17:18.637 --> 17:22.131
Oh, I see, everything nice
and legal, huh?

17:22.241 --> 17:25.040
"Henceforth this joint is ours."

17:27.113 --> 17:29.013
You needed a lawyer for that?

17:29.115 --> 17:31.413
Sure, he put in
the "henceforth."

17:31.517 --> 17:34.077
AL: Well, guys, I don't want
to be a party pooper,

17:34.186 --> 17:36.848
but I can't sign that.

17:36.956 --> 17:40.290
Oh, I think our partner
needs a little persuading.

17:40.393 --> 17:41.792
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

17:41.894 --> 17:43.328
No, wait, wait.
No, wait a minute, now.

17:43.429 --> 17:44.897
You know, I didn't
tell you this before,

17:44.997 --> 17:46.055
but I already have a partner,

17:46.165 --> 17:48.566
so I guess you boys
can just run along.

17:48.668 --> 17:51.296
Hey, how about some
nice burgers to go, okay?

17:51.404 --> 17:53.771
What is this, a double cross?

17:53.873 --> 17:55.432
Oh, no, no, no,
I wouldn't double-cross you.

17:55.541 --> 17:58.340
No, it's my partner, Mr. Big.

17:58.444 --> 18:00.071
Mr. Big.

18:00.179 --> 18:01.271
HOLLOWAY:
Mr. Big?

18:01.380 --> 18:02.779
What is it, a candy bar?

18:02.882 --> 18:04.748
No.
He's the leader of a gang.

18:04.850 --> 18:06.784
The meanest, toughest gang
in Milwaukee.

18:06.886 --> 18:08.376
And I'll tell you guys
something.

18:08.487 --> 18:10.649
He wouldn't like the idea
of you guys hanging around here.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.690
Oh, Mr. Big is tough, huh?

18:12.792 --> 18:15.261
Oh... tough, tough.

18:15.361 --> 18:16.954
HOLLOWAY:
Claw...

18:17.063 --> 18:19.191
show him tough.

18:26.272 --> 18:28.934
Ah, gee, I just filled that.

18:30.209 --> 18:32.337
Don't nobody move.

18:32.445 --> 18:35.073
Right, Scarf ace?

18:35.181 --> 18:37.240
Scarf ace?

18:39.552 --> 18:40.576
I surrender.

18:40.686 --> 18:42.586
Won't you put your hands down?

18:42.688 --> 18:44.383
Come on.

18:44.490 --> 18:46.322
Who are these punks?

18:46.425 --> 18:47.824
Oh, these guys aren't punks.

18:47.927 --> 18:49.725
They're part of Mr. Big's gang.

18:49.829 --> 18:50.990
You see that guy right there?

18:51.097 --> 18:52.895
That's Scarf ace Malph.

18:52.999 --> 18:54.933
He don't have no scar.

18:55.034 --> 18:56.559
Yeah, how about that?

18:56.669 --> 18:58.637
Oh, w-well, you see,
m-my skin's cleared up a lot.

18:58.738 --> 19:00.467
I cut out sweets.

19:00.573 --> 19:03.474
Yeah, and this guy--
the Undertaker.

19:03.576 --> 19:05.271
Yeah.

19:07.213 --> 19:09.910
Simple pine box, medium.

19:10.016 --> 19:12.178
I've had enough of this--
Claw.

19:12.284 --> 19:13.752
RALPH:
Claw!

19:13.853 --> 19:16.049
(nasal voice):
Freeze!

19:21.961 --> 19:24.191
I don't want no muscles moved.

19:24.296 --> 19:26.196
No muscles moved
until Mr. Big gets here,

19:26.298 --> 19:28.232
gets here, gets here, gets here.

19:33.172 --> 19:34.401
You're bluffing.

19:34.507 --> 19:35.941
There's no Mr. Big.

19:36.042 --> 19:38.033
No Mr. Big?

19:38.144 --> 19:40.408
(nasal cackling)

19:40.513 --> 19:43.813
Mr. Big.

19:54.794 --> 19:56.819
You lose, bullet brain.

19:56.929 --> 19:58.624
I'm Mr. Big.

19:58.731 --> 20:00.859
What kind of a name is Mr. Big?

20:00.966 --> 20:02.991
- Polish.
- German. -Russian.

20:04.270 --> 20:07.262
Hey, Al, what are these ants
doing in my place, huh?

20:07.373 --> 20:08.636
They want to take over Arnold's.

20:08.741 --> 20:10.266
They want to cut in
on your turf.

20:10.376 --> 20:12.037
Is that so?

20:12.144 --> 20:14.511
Psycho Louis,
tell them how I feel

20:14.613 --> 20:16.877
about that particular situation.

20:16.982 --> 20:19.076
(cackling)

20:19.185 --> 20:21.415
Mr. Big don't like
no uninvited guests

20:21.520 --> 20:23.511
in his joint,
in his joint, in his joint.

20:25.224 --> 20:27.249
So you guys better cut out
before we cut in.

20:27.359 --> 20:28.793
Before we cut in.
(cackles)

20:28.894 --> 20:30.919
See? You get it?

20:31.030 --> 20:33.089
Uh, I think they got it, Louis.

20:33.199 --> 20:34.428
RICHIE:
Cut, cut cut!

20:34.533 --> 20:35.898
Slice, slice, slice!

20:36.001 --> 20:38.231
I'm gonna make a jigsaw puzzle
out of the bunch of youse,

20:38.337 --> 20:39.736
the bunch of youse,
the bunch of youse.

20:39.839 --> 20:41.000
-(cackles)
- It's all right, Psycho.

20:41.107 --> 20:42.871
- Take it easy. Yeah.
- You can play later, Louie.

20:42.975 --> 20:44.966
I want to eat their watches.
(cackles)

20:45.077 --> 20:46.408
I want to eat your watches.

20:46.512 --> 20:48.480
He eats watches?

20:48.581 --> 20:51.380
Oh, yeah. Yeah, he starts at
the fingers and eats his way up.

20:51.484 --> 20:53.452
Yeah. Unless you're
wearing a pocket watch.

20:53.552 --> 20:56.487
Then... I don't even want
to talk about it.

20:59.925 --> 21:01.620
Now that you've met my family,

21:01.727 --> 21:04.458
why don't you get out of here
while you're still able?

21:04.563 --> 21:06.691
Yeah, there's a bus leaving
in five minutes.

21:06.799 --> 21:08.790
Be under it.

21:10.035 --> 21:12.936
I like it here, Mr. Small.

21:14.240 --> 21:15.833
Mr. Small?

21:15.941 --> 21:18.239
Oh, let me convince him.
I want to convince him.

21:18.344 --> 21:20.438
Cut, cut, slice, slice.

21:20.546 --> 21:23.106
Oh, that was good.

21:23.215 --> 21:25.206
Pass it on.

21:25.317 --> 21:28.150
(giggles) Pass it on.

21:28.254 --> 21:29.983
Pass it on.

21:31.624 --> 21:32.682
Pass it on.

21:32.792 --> 21:34.658
Ooh, ooh! No!
I didn't mean that!

21:34.760 --> 21:36.990
That was from them,
not-not from me.

21:37.096 --> 21:40.066
Didn't you guys ever play
that game, "Pass It On"?

21:40.166 --> 21:42.760
Nobody ever did that
to me before.

21:42.868 --> 21:45.565
These guys are tough.
Come on.

21:46.672 --> 21:48.401
POTSIE:
They're leaving.

21:48.507 --> 21:50.532
RALPH:
I don't think so. (yelps)

21:50.643 --> 21:52.372
HOLLOWAY:
Get 'em, boys.

21:52.478 --> 21:53.968
(yelling)

21:54.079 --> 21:55.376
POTSIE:
Look out! Look out!

21:55.481 --> 21:56.778
AL:
I got you, Claw!

21:56.882 --> 21:58.611
-(fingers snapping)
- FONZIE: Hold it.

21:58.717 --> 21:59.912
(others yelling)

22:00.019 --> 22:02.681
AL:
I got you! Take that!

22:02.788 --> 22:04.552
Take that!

22:05.958 --> 22:07.926
Oh.

22:08.027 --> 22:09.859
I'm sorry.

22:09.962 --> 22:12.158
Sit down. Get down.

22:14.433 --> 22:15.832
That's just
a little game we play

22:15.935 --> 22:17.425
before we get started,
all right?

22:17.536 --> 22:19.834
Now, it's just me and you,
Mr. "Hallway."

22:19.939 --> 22:21.236
No, it isn't.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.206
Claw does my dirty work.

22:23.309 --> 22:24.435
Is that so?

22:24.543 --> 22:27.240
Show him, Claw.

22:37.857 --> 22:39.188
Uh-oh.

22:52.805 --> 22:55.399
-(metallic creaking)
-(Claw groaning)

23:00.746 --> 23:03.147
Look what he did.

23:03.249 --> 23:04.614
He busted my claw.

23:04.717 --> 23:06.207
I got no claw.

23:06.318 --> 23:08.047
What are they gonna call me now?

23:08.153 --> 23:10.588
Lefty. Get out of the way.

23:10.689 --> 23:12.316
Your turn. Let's go.

23:12.424 --> 23:13.619
No, no, no, it's your turf.

23:13.726 --> 23:15.285
Come on, let's get out of here.

23:15.394 --> 23:16.589
There they are. There they are.

23:16.695 --> 23:18.459
- I told you-- right here.
- POTSIE: We did it.

23:18.564 --> 23:20.828
Wait, we're just trying...
we were going to buy the place.

23:20.933 --> 23:21.798
- Richard!
-ls everyone all right?

23:21.901 --> 23:23.391
- Oh, Richard.
- You all right?

23:23.502 --> 23:25.027
(nasal voice): I'm fine!
I'm fine, I'm fine, I'm fine!

23:25.137 --> 23:26.229
I'm telling you, I'm fine!

23:26.338 --> 23:27.464
- I'll be okay!
- Oh!

23:27.573 --> 23:28.734
Oh, my-

23:28.841 --> 23:30.400
Somebody must have
hit him in the head.

23:30.509 --> 23:32.034
Nobody him me in the head.
No, no.

23:32.144 --> 23:33.543
We did the hitting
and the cutting

23:33.646 --> 23:34.977
and the slicing, and, boy...

23:35.080 --> 23:37.174
(normal voice):
We did real well.

23:38.217 --> 23:40.743
(indistinct chatter)

23:49.395 --> 23:50.624
MARION:
Oh, boys,

23:50.729 --> 23:52.254
these-these suits
and these hats.

23:52.364 --> 23:53.854
Well, it's just...
it's just a wonder

23:53.966 --> 23:55.434
